abstract: >-
  This work develops the third stage of the Boundary-Condition Quantum Mechanics
  (BCQM) programme. It introduces a hop-bounded, retarded growth model for
  quantum event chains in an emergent spacetime regime, and shows how classical
  inertial motion and an effective mass scaling m_eff ‚àù W_coh^{-2} arise from
  finite coherence horizon and phase-coherent propagation.
